Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.62,0:00:13.33,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,2000)\fsp-8\t(1500,3000,\bord4)\pos(677,146)\c&H000000&\t(0,400,\c&HFFFFFF)\bord3\3c&HABA5E7&}Feathers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.66,0:00:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The powdery snow flutters down, coloring the mountain ridge white
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.07,0:00:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The two inside a run-down house in a desolate village
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}huddle together in the winter night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.65,0:00:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"It'd also been snowing the day we'd met,"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.99,0:00:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}you murmured with a smile
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.23,0:00:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}And I'd hidden my face flushed from the hearth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.23,0:01:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fade(0,700)}within the shadow of your large sleeve
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.18,0:01:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}With a breath of joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.45,0:01:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}I sang of spring's arrival along with the chirping birds
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.45,0:01:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"Your voice is beautiful," you told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.06,0:01:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}and that alone, just those words, made me so happy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.87,0:01:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"If someday, I no longer had this beautiful voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.77,0:01:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}would you still, even then, love me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.18,0:01:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"Of course," you said, smiling gently
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.49,0:01:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fade(0,2000)}as your large hand softly stroked my cheek
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.35,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}One leaf-lit summer afternoon, you collapsed from illness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.36,0:02:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}Our poor married life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.26,0:02:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}couldn't afford the medicine to cure it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.27,0:02:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The next day, along with the following,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.40,0:02:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}I did nothing but intently weave
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}I wouldn't let your life
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.25,0:02:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}fall like the short-lived autumn leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.05,0:02:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The seasons flow by
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.75,0:02:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The bell crickets mark the end of summer with their cries
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.39,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"Your fingers are beautiful," you told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}gripping my wound-covered hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}but yours were much too cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.23,0:03:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"If someday, I no longer had these beautiful fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}would you still, even then, love me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.81,0:03:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"Of course," you said, coughing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.91,0:03:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}as your large hands caressed my hurting fingers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:28.35,Default Upper,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\pos(427,335)}Day and night, don't stop weaving
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:32.39,Default Upper,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\pos(427,335)}Hurry, hurry, I need to buy the medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.39,0:03:36.36,Default Upper,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\pos(427,335)}Just a bit more, ony a bit more; before the autumn leaves fall
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:43.50,Default Upper,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fade(0,1250)\pos(427,335)}Until these fingers can't move... Until these feathers are used up...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:31.32,Default Lower,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー{\fs\fn} Ah, the sunset's breeze {\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.32,0:03:35.63,Default Lower,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー{\fs\fn} sways the ruthlessly decaying fruit's flame {\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:43.50,Default Lower,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fade(0,1250)\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー{\fs\fn} until it falls {\fnＭＳ 明朝\fs20}ー
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"If someday, I were no longer a human,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}would you still love me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.02,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}The truth left unable to be told, in fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.23,0:04:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}I softly pluck the final feather alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}"Of course," I say, smiling
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.30,0:04:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}as I embrace you, who has lost your wings
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}And that crane which had beautifully taken flight that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}I've never forgotten, and still remember, even now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}{\fade(0,2000)}And just like always, I love you
